  "summary": "Malicious code in @emilgroup/commission-sdk (npm)",
  "details": "\n---\n_-= Per source details. Do not edit below this line.=-_\n\n## Source: amazon-inspector (88cda98ba417752b6bf4aef7eb0ecf7410017226165423202ca4d5886f370478)\nThe package @emilgroup/commission-sdk was found to contain malicious code.\n\n## Source: google-open-source-security (0747507ecb5327b6cd870cff26e8ef8ed455330e757b920c725988c9d36b7b7d)\nThis package was compromised by the CanisterWorm campaign by the TeamPCP\nthreat actor. The malicious payload establishes persistence as user systemd\nservice and places a backdoor on the infected host. The malware will also\nharvest npm credentials and can autonomously spread.\n",
